<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>While using Zend_Acl, I encountered a problem that can be reproduce with this simple code :</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$acl = new Zend_Acl();
$acl-&gt;addRole('admin');
$acl-&gt;addResource('blog');
$acl-&gt;allow('admin', 'blog', 'read');
$acl-&gt;removeAllow(array('admin'), array('blog'), null);
</code></pre>

<p>It results with this :</p>

<pre class="literal">
Notice:  Undefined index:  allPrivileges in lib/Zend/Acl.php on line 682
</pre>

<p>The documentation (<a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.acl.refining.html#zend.acl.refining.removing">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a>) indicate that it should remove allow rights to every privileges in the ACL.</p>

